<h4> PARI/GP </h4>It is possible to use a program in Pari&#58; for that, put it between parenthesis&#58; for example, the lines

!set tmp0=!randitem 0,1

!set m_a=$(tmp0) 


!set tmp0=!randint 10, 100

!set m_b=$[rint($(tmp0))]


!set t_=!replace internal \( by ( in (f(n)=local(m) ; m=if(n==0, n, factor($m_b)));print(f($m_a))
!set tmp0=!exec pari $t_

!set m_N=$(tmp0) 

<p><tt> 
<br>\def{text a=random(0,1)}
<br>\def{integer b=randint(10..100)}
<br>\def{text N=pari((f(n)=local(m) ; m=if(n==0, n, factor(\b)));print(f(\a)))}</tt>
</p>
Example&#58; output  the factorisation of  $m_b if some random number  a=$m_a equals 0 et 0 otherwise &#58; 
N=$m_N (try 
