)
<p>
The Pari command <tt>random </tt> de Pari/GP is  incompatible with WIMS' one ; so write <tt> random&#92;(125) </tt> in Pari/GP. In this cases,<tt> random </tt> is sent to Pari/GP with no interpretation but "\" is taken away.
<p>

!set t_=!replace internal \( by ( in print(matrix(4,5,i,j,random\(257)))
!set tmp0=!exec pari $t_

!set m_A=$(tmp0) 

 Example &#58; define a matrix of size 4,5 with random coefficients between  0 and 256 &#58; 
<center> 
!insmath A= [\A]
</center>
